{"comments":"Submodular Function Classification Types.\n\nMonotonicity and curvature classification for submodular functions.\nThese properties determine achievable approximation ratios.\n\n## Monotonicity\n\n- **Monotone**: f(A) ≤ f(B) whenever A ⊆ B (adding elements never decreases value)\n- **NonMonotone**: f(A) can exceed f(B) even when A ⊆ B\n\n## Curvature\n\nCurvature κ ∈ [0, 1] measures how far from modular (additive) f is:\n- κ = 0: f is modular (linear)\n- κ = 1: f has maximum submodularity\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Prelude (Eq, Ord, Show)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[64,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[64,3]},"title":"Monotone"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[65,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[65,3]},"title":"NonMonotone"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"Monotonicity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[67,50],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[67,1]},"title":"eqMonotonicity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"Monotonicity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[68,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[68,1]},"title":"ordMonotonicity"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Types","Classification"],"Monotonicity"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[72,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[70,1]},"title":"showMonotonicity"}],"comments":"Monotonicity classification of a submodular function.\n\n**Monotone**: f(A) ≤ f(B) whenever A ⊆ B\n  - Adding elements never decreases value\n  - Achievable approximation ratio: (1 - 1/e) ≈ 0.632\n\n**NonMonotone**: f(A) can be > f(B) even when A ⊆ B\n  - Adding elements may decrease value\n  - Achievable approximation ratio: 1/2\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"data","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[65,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[63,1]},"title":"Monotonicity"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[87,3]},"title":"CurvatureUnknown"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[88,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[88,3]},"title":"CurvatureBounded"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[89,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Types/Classification.purs","start":[89,3]},"title":"CurvatureExact"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotati